HEADWORD: Haply
<hw>Hap"ly</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧p"l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>By hap,
chance, luck, or accident; perhaps; it may be.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lest <qex>haply</qex> ye be found even to fight against God.</q>
<rj><qau>Acts v. 39.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Happed</ent>⟦br⟧
